  "text": "Fennel is a flowering plant from family Apiaceae which has been used as a medicinal plant in TPM due to its known antioxidative, anti-inflammatory, estrogenic, diuretic, emmenagogue, antithrombotic, and antihypertensive features [CITATION_1] . This plant has been found to be effective in inducing menstruation after medroxyprogesterone acetate use in comparison to control group [CITATION_2] .",
